    "body": "When I apply the following patch to the downloaded source code, it succeeds to compile:\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff -uNr grpc-1.0.1.orig/config.m4 grpc-1.0.1/config.m4\r\n--- grpc-1.0.1.orig/config.m4   2017-01-09 10:44:47.183344848 -0800\r\n+++ grpc-1.0.1/config.m4        2017-01-09 10:45:12.175182042 -0800\r\n@@ -5,9 +5,9 @@\r\n   dnl Write more examples of tests here...\r\n \r\n   dnl # --with-grpc -> add include path\r\n-  PHP_ADD_INCLUDE(../../grpc/include)\r\n-  PHP_ADD_INCLUDE(../../grpc/src/php/ext/grpc)\r\n-  PHP_ADD_INCLUDE(../../grpc/third_party/boringssl/include)\r\n+  PHP_ADD_INCLUDE(./include)\r\n+  PHP_ADD_INCLUDE(./src/php/ext/grpc)\r\n+  PHP_ADD_INCLUDE(./third_party/boringssl/include)\r\n \r\n   LIBS=\"-lpthread $LIBS\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nMaybe I can just add this patch before calling phpize for now, but does it make sense to apply it to `templates/config.m4.template`?"
